Crimson Dunes
Crimson Dunes is one of the proposed names for the desert-themed map, representing a post-apocalyptic battleground.<SEP>One of the proposed names for the desert-themed map in Project TOG.<SEP>One of the proposed names for the desert-themed map in Project TOG.

Outpost
Outposts are key strategic points on the map where players engage in combat to gain territorial control.<SEP>Strategic locations on the map where players engage in combat and resource control.<SEP>Strategic locations on the map where players engage in combat and resource control.

Project TOG
Project TOG is the governing project under which the desert environment map design guidelines are being developed.<SEP>An organization responsible for developing map design guidelines for a desert environment in a game.<SEP>An organization responsible for developing map design guidelines for a desert environment in a game.

Desert Environment
The Desert Environment represents the barren, post-apocalyptic setting that serves as the thematic backdrop of the map.<SEP>The desert environment serves as the setting for the map, featuring arid landscapes and remnants of military bases.<SEP>The desert environment serves as the setting for the map, featuring arid landscapes and remnants of military bases.

Khamsin Outpost
Khamsin Outpost refers to a specific area within the desert map, previously a military base now turned into a strategic conflict zone.<SEP>A third proposed name for the desert-themed map in Project TOG.<SEP>A third proposed name for the desert-themed map in Project TOG.

Rust Frontier
Rust Frontier is another proposed name for the desert-themed map, symbolizing an arid wasteland with remnants of military structures.<SEP>Another proposed name for the desert-themed map in Project TOG.<SEP>Another proposed name for the desert-themed map in Project TOG.

Demo Map Design File
The Demo Map Design file is a document containing guidelines and specifications for designing a desert-themed map for Project TOG.<SEP>A design file used for creating maps in the game Project TOG.<SEP>A design file used for creating maps in the game Project TOG.

Tank
Tanks are vehicles used by competing factions in the game for strategic control over the desert map.<SEP>Vehicles used by players in the game, designed to interact with terrain mechanics.<SEP>Vehicles used by players in the game, designed to interact with terrain mechanics.

Terrain
Terrain refers to the physical features of the map such as sand dunes, slopes, and other environmental elements that influence gameplay dynamics.

Flank Route
Flank Routes are alternative paths designed to allow scouts to apply pressure by attacking from unexpected angles.<SEP>A gameplay element allowing Scout tanks to apply unexpected pressure during battles.<SEP>A gameplay element allowing Scout tanks to apply unexpected pressure during battles.

Storm Event
Storm Event is a dynamic in-game occurrence that temporarily reduces visibility due to wind and sandstorms.<SEP>A dynamic weather event that temporarily reduces visibility with sandstorms.<SEP>A dynamic weather event that temporarily reduces visibility with sandstorms.

NavMesh Modifier
NavMesh Modifier is a tool used in Unity to define areas like sinking sand and ramps for optimal pathfinding in the game.<SEP>A Unity setup tool used to create interactive terrain features like quicksand and ramps.<SEP>A Unity setup tool used to create interactive terrain features like quicksand and ramps.

Lighting Bake
Lighting Bake is a technique in Unity to precompute static lighting and shadows for improved performance.<SEP>A Unity technique used to generate static lighting effects on terrain while keeping tank shadows dynamic.<SEP>A Unity technique used to generate static lighting effects on terrain while keeping tank shadows dynamic.

Choke Point
Choke Points are narrow passages strategically placed on the map to encourage concentrated and natural engagements between players.

Secret Tunnel
Secret Tunnels provide teleportation points between flank lanes, adding a strategic element to the gameplay.<SEP>Hidden tunnels allowing fast travel between flank lanes with a cooldown period.<SEP>Hidden tunnels allowing fast travel between flank lanes with a cooldown period.

Combat Zone
Combat Zones are designated areas surrounding outposts where intense player-versus-player battles occur.<SEP>Areas surrounding outposts where most of the fighting occurs, providing cover and flanking routes.<SEP>Areas surrounding outposts where most of the fighting occurs, providing cover and flanking routes.

Prefab
Prefabs are reusable assets in Unity such as containers, bunkers, and walls used to construct the map's architecture.

Unity Setup
Unity Setup refers to the technical configuration process used to implement the map design within the Unity game engine.

Gameplay Notes
Gameplay Notes provide insights into how the terrain and environmental factors affect player strategies during matches.

Scout
Scouts are units or roles within the game designed to utilize flank routes for tactical advantages.<SEP>Scout is the smallest class of tank, characterized by its speed and agility in combat scenarios.

Visibility
Visibility refers to the clarity of sight within the game environment, often affected by dynamic events like Storm Events.

Combat

Map Architecture

Static Terrain

Dynamic Tank Shadow

Match

Concrete Ruins

Radar Station

Quicksand

Container
Rusted containers that are part of the environmental details within the map.<SEP>Rusted containers that are part of the environmental details within the map.

High Ground
Elevated areas on the map that provide strategic advantages such as increased visibility and sniping positions.<SEP>Elevated areas on the map that provide strategic advantages such as increased visibility and sniping positions.

Kill Count
The expected total number of kills for both teams during a match.<SEP>The expected total number of kills for both teams during a match.

Scout Tank
A type of tank in the game designed to utilize flank routes for tactical advantages.<SEP>A type of tank in the game designed to utilize flank routes for tactical advantages.

Secret tunnels add a hidden mechanic allowing players to traverse the map quickly between specific lanes.

Heavy Tank
Teamfights are designed to leverage the high damage output of heavy tanks during large-scale engagements.

Tank Decorations
Tank Decorations refer to the link between tanks and decoration items, indicating which decorations a player owns or has applied.

Player Quests
Player Quests track the progress and status of quests completed or in progress by individual players.

Tank Artifacts
Tank Artifacts represent the association between tanks and artifacts, showing which artifacts a player owns or has equipped.

Quests
Quests define objectives and rewards within the game, categorized as daily, weekly, or event-based.

Decorations
Decorations are items used for tank customization, including wraps, decals, and stickers.<SEP>Decorations are small map elements that players can pass through and do not interact with significantly.

data.content:
Artifacts
Artifacts are special items that provide buffs to tanks, stored in a master data list.

Tanks
Tanks are vehicles owned by players, with attributes like speed, damage, and fire rate. They can be customized with decorations and artifacts.

Players
Players represent the accounts of users participating in the game, with attributes such as name, level, gold, diamonds, and achievements.

Purchases
Purchases log the transaction history of players, including items bought using gold, diamonds, or real money.

Match Players
Match Players represent the association between players and their performance metrics in matches, including kills, deaths, assists, and scores.

Matches
Matches represent individual game sessions, storing information about start/end times, game modes, and winning teams.

Garage
Garage refers to the system allowing players to customize their tanks with decorations and artifacts.

Unity
Unity is a software platform used as the default measurement system for object dimensions in the game design process.

Grass Logic Design
Grass Logic Design refers to the system logic governing the behavior and functionality of grass within the game map to enhance tactical depth.<SEP>Grass Logic Design is a reference document detailing the behavior and characteristics of the HI_Grass hiding object in the game.

H THNG LOGIC CA C XANH
H THNG LOGIC CA C XANH is the Vietnamese title for the Grass Logic Design document, describing the logic system of grass within the game.

Skills
Skills refer to the game mechanics or abilities influenced by the grass logic design, impacting gameplay interactions.

Block Object
Block Objects are map elements that players and projectiles cannot pass through, serving as obstacles or boundaries.

BO_Collider
BO_Collider is a type of Block Object used as a map boundary in the game.

BO_Container
BO_Container is a type of Block Object with variants differing in dimensions and color.

BO_Mountain
BO_Mountain is a type of Block Object representing a mountain in the game.

BO_Building
BO_Building is a type of Block Object in the game that players and projectiles cannot pass through.

Map Design Document
The Map Design Document is a guide that describes and categorizes important objects used in the maps of the World Tank War game.

BO_Rock
BO_Rock is a type of Block Object representing a rock in the game.

BO_Sign
BO_Sign is a type of Block Object representing a sign in the game.

BR_Deco
BR_Deco is a type of Breakable Object in the game that can be destroyed by projectiles.

BR_Barrel
BR_Barrel is a type of Breakable Object in the game that can be destroyed by projectiles.

DE_Deco
DE_Deco is a type of Decoration in the game that players can pass through.

Breakable Object
Breakable Objects are map elements that players cannot pass through but can be destroyed by projectiles.

BR_Cactus
BR_Cactus is a type of Breakable Object in the game that can be destroyed by projectiles.

BR_Gate
BR_Gate is a type of Breakable Object in the game that can be destroyed by projectiles.

Ground
Ground objects are map elements that players cannot pass through and serve as the floor or terrain.

Hiding Object
Hiding Objects are map elements that players and projectiles can pass through, providing stealth capabilities to players.

GR_Ground
GR_Ground is a type of Ground object in the game that serves as the floor or terrain.

HI_Grass
HI_Grass is a type of Hiding Object in the game that allows players to become invisible when inside it.

Outpost Design - Base Capture Mode
Outpost Design - Base Capture Mode is a reference document detailing the behavior and destruction mechanics of Outpost Objects like OP_Tower in the game.

Outpost Object
Outpost Objects are map elements that players and projectiles cannot pass through, except for specific tank team projectiles designed to destroy them.

OP_Tower
OP_Tower is a specific type of outpost structure within the game, designed for defensive purposes.<SEP>OP_Tower is a type of Outpost Object in the game that serves as a base structure that can be targeted and destroyed by specific tank team projectiles.

BO_Container Variant
BO_Container Variant refers to modified versions of BO_Container with altered dimensions and colors.

Tank War
Tank War represents a game mode involving combat between tanks and strategic objectives like base capture.

Tank Team ATK
Tank Team ATK is a group capable of destroying outposts with their tank ammunition.

Combat Module
Combat Module refers to a system component related to the design and functionality of outposts in the Base Capture Mode.

Tank (TA)
Tank (TA) refers to in-game tank objects that cannot pass through each other and have specific interactions with ammunition.

Outpost Design
Outpost Design describes structures used as strategic points in the game, which can be destroyed by tank ammunition.

Base Capture Mode
Base Capture Mode is a gameplay mode focused on capturing enemy bases using tanks and other combat assets.

Tank System Detail
Tank System Detail outlines the specifications and behavior of different tank classes in the game.

Character Module
Character Module is a system component detailing the characteristics and classifications of tanks in Tank War.

Assault
Assault is a medium-sized tank class offering a balance between speed and firepower in combat.

Heavy
Heavy is the largest and most powerful tank class, known for its durability and high damage output.

Mode Outpost Breaker
Mode Outpost Breaker is a game mode where players aim to destroy enemy outposts using tanks and other weapons.

Mode Deathmatch
Mode Deathmatch is a free-for-all game mode where players compete to achieve the highest score by eliminating opponents.

DE
DE refers to the smallest measurable object within the game environment.

GameAssets
GameAssets refers to the directory containing models and assets for Tank Wars, including tank models.

Unity Unit
Unity Unit is the default measurement unit in Unity, where 1 meter equals 1 Unity Unit.
